  <summary>09/19/1995--Introduced.
Congressional Pay Accountability Act of 1995 - Repeals provisions of Federal law which appropriate funds for compensation of Members of Congress at levels authorized by law and recommended by the President for Federal employees for a fiscal year (thus subjecting congressional pay to annual appropriations).</summary>
